  <brief_title>Aquacel Compared to Traditional Post Surgical Wound Dressing in Vascular Surgery Patients</brief_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Rigshospitalet, Denmark</agency>
      <agency_class>Other</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Rigshospitalet, Denmark</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is a prospective randomised, controlled study of 136 patients undergoing vascular
      surgery. Their closed wounds were covered with either aquacel, a hydrofiber dressing, or a
      traditional gauze dressing.Number of changes, patient comfort,number of infections, length of
      hospital stay and wound complications were compared between the two groups.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
